article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- — Kenyon Giles scored 25 points as UNC Greensboro beat High Point 72-68 on Tuesday night. Giles went 11 of 21 from the field (2 for 7 from 3-point range) for the Spartans (4-4). Jalen Breath added 16 points and 10 rebounds. Joryam Saizonou finished with with 15 points. Kimani Hamilton led the way for the Panthers (8-2) with 13 points. High Point also got 11 points and four assists from Kezza Giffa. D'Maurian Williams finished with 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
